s that aren't suppressible with dexamethasone.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035741,0.065267,0.08401,0.092014,0.10141,0.10285,0.10165,0.098776,0.094083,0.087688,0.074845,0.061671],"unified_progress":[0.035418,0.067666,0.086586,0.095985,0.10115,0.1051,0.10244,0.098229,0.093067,0.087983,0.072329,0.054048]},{"section":11,"text":"ACTH is produced by the pituitary gland and stimulates the adrenal glands to release cortisol.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044286,0.063446,0.080213,0.092653,0.10214,0.10464,0.10482,0.1008,0.094482,0.083324,0.070967,0.058224],"unified_progress":[0.047828,0.077095,0.09268,0.099973,0.10516,0.10287,0.1021,0.093579,0.088119,0.078352,0.064933,0.047306]},{"section":12,"text":"If the ACTH level is high and doesn't drop after giving a high dose of dexamethasone, it suggests that the body isn't responding normally to the glucocorticoid.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.041109,0.062922,0.078518,0.089391,0.098972,0.10247,0.10345,0.1013,0.097337,0.087308,0.075443,0.061784],"unified_progress":[0.041801,0.072083,0.088868,0.096329,0.10232,0.10555,0.10441,0.095542,0.089521,0.081973,0.069294,0.05231]},{"section":13,"text":"This is called an \"unsuppressible\" ACTH level.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036027,0.064793,0.081982,0.093763,0.097717,0.099637,0.10118,0.099259,0.095297,0.087365,0.077202,0.065779],"unified_progress":[0.037707,0.067675,0.085567,0.095486,0.10066,0.10282,0.10246,0.09768,0.092802,0.086133,0.073405,0.057601]},{"section":14,"text":"Unsuppressible ACTH can be seen in conditions where the body's feedback mechanism is disrupted.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03833,0.058527,0.075066,0.086222,0.096312,0.10075,0.10365,0.10315,0.099911,0.092006,0.079967,0.066106],"unified_progress":[0.041279,0.068844,0.084782,0.093803,0.099794,0.10246,0.10139,0.097606,0.092956,0.087111,0.073662,0.056314]},{"section":15,"text":"One possibility is a pituitary tumor that's secreting ACTH (like a pituitary adenoma), but that's less likely here because the patient has other symptoms pointing towards a lung issue.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036234,0.061262,0.075339,0.085813,0.093672,0.098205,0.10329,0.10344,0.10091,0.093353,0.081509,0.066974],"unified_progress":[0.040388,0.067883,0.083058,0.092186,0.097753,0.10114,0.099815,0.098147,0.094824,0.088743,0.075879,0.060185]},{"section":16,"text":"Another possibility is an ectopic ACTH secretion.","dimension":5,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026268,0.048906,0.068516,0.080998,0.094145,0.10221,0.10777,0.1097,0.10749,0.10159,0.085344,0.067065],"unified_progress":[0.03224,0.064797,0.084818,0.097445,0.10083,0.10452,0.10404,0.10023,0.09499,0.090099,0.072826,0.053164]},{"section":17,"text":"This happens when a tumor outside the pituitary gland, often in the lungs, produces ACTH.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03212,0.054452,0.072188,0.085315,0.096326,0.10239,0.10849,0.10797,0.10451,0.093576,0.079791,0.062868],"unified_progress":[0.037036,0.067414,0.087026,0.099765,0.10539,0.10774,0.10409,0.09938,0.094868,0.082625,0.065733,0.048929]},{"section":18,"text":"This is commonly associated with small cell lung cancer, which can secrete various hormones, including ACTH.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031219,0.05341,0.070013,0.082333,0.094165,0.10076,0.10887,0.11065,0.10624,0.095937,0.0814,0.065001],"unified_progress":[0.034404,0.061857,0.08236,0.094682,0.10031,0.1128,0.10571,0.1014,0.095041,0.087946,0.070866,0.052623]},{"section":19,"text":"This condition is known as ectopic ACTH syndrome.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030416,0.055656,0.071728,0.08388,0.092933,0.098401,0.10606,0.10772,0.10308,0.095232,0.083361,0.071535],"unified_progress":[0.032193,0.059441,0.080189,0.093452,0.099029,0.10619,0.10487,0.10218,0.096655,0.090076,0.075466,0.060263]},{"section":20,"text":"Given that the patient is a smoker, has a history of hemoptysis, and an elevated ACTH level that doesn't suppress, it points towards small cell lung cancer.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036626,0.062135,0.066544,0.07105,0.078734,0.083608,0.088408,0.092604,0.095625,0.10132,0.10662,0.11673],"unified_progress":[0.036756,0.058592,0.067253,0.075154,0.080308,0.08971,0.088732,0.094172,0.095067,0.095257,0.10424,0.11476]},{"section":21,"text":"Small cell lung cancer is a type of lung cancer that grows quickly and often spreads early.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035485,0.05837,0.07021,0.080257,0.088706,0.093921,0.10358,0.10664,0.10314,0.097473,0.086161,0.076063],"unified_progress":[0.032207,0.057388,0.078593,0.088582,0.095836,0.1044,0.10399,0.10379,0.099994,0.094975,0.079258,0.06098]},{"section":22,"text":"It's also known to produce ectopic hormones, including ACTH.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032547,0.053268,0.068327,0.079474,0.091396,0.098114,0.10591,0.10854,0.10635,0.09809,0.086571,0.071414],"unified_progress":[0.03598,0.061215,0.079159,0.090341,0.097189,0.10337,0.10272,0.10182,0.097942,0.092992,0.077267,0.060009]},{"section":23,"text":"So, putting it all together: chronic smoking, hemoptysis, and an unresponsive ACTH level make me think of small cell lung cancer with ectopic ACTH secretion.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026589,0.046541,0.056324,0.063132,0.071855,0.077604,0.083235,0.089526,0.094056,0.1099,0.12557,0.15567],"unified_progress":[0.028823,0.048755,0.057706,0.066609,0.07121,0.081705,0.082415,0.090773,0.095194,0.099213,0.12353,0.15406]},{"section":24,"text":"This would explain the hypertension as well, since excess ACTH can lead to high blood pressure due to increased cortisol levels (Cushing's syndrome).","dimension":13,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036761,0.050586,0.066562,0.076443,0.085267,0.090821,0.097121,0.1015,0.10368,0.10252,0.097709,0.091037],"unified_progress":[0.035338,0.053786,0.06839,0.077239,0.085606,0.093263,0.095565,0.099456,0.10113,0.10191,0.098352,0.089964]},{"section":25,"text":"I don't think it's a pituitary issue because the patient's symptoms are more consistent with a lung primary tumor.","dimension":0,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033344,0.055572,0.066357,0.073767,0.081627,0.086849,0.092527,0.096808,0.10038,0.1054,0.1043,0.10307],"unified_progress":[0.033087,0.055587,0.066204,0.074933,0.081714,0.087584,0.09094,0.09747,0.10016,0.10462,0.10458,0.10313]},{"section":26,"text":"Also, truncal obesity and hypertension are classic signs of Cushing's syndrome, which aligns with the ectopic ACTH production.","dimension":3,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029136,0.047586,0.064219,0.074841,0.085634,0.09236,0.09934,0.10376,0.10557,0.10452,0.099694,0.093347],"unified_progress":[0.030219,0.051041,0.065894,0.075448,0.083748,0.092063,0.094462,0.099719,0.10164,0.104,0.1023,0.099464]},{"section":27,"text":"Therefore, the most likely diagnosis is small cell lung cancer.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.017676,0.032392,0.042258,0.048498,0.05724,0.063999,0.069866,0.080491,0.089312,0.12558,0.15671,0.21598],"unified_progress":[0.016286,0.031549,0.040392,0.05122,0.055902,0.068285,0.072811,0.086328,0.097357,0.11017,0.15297,0.21673]},{"section":28,"text":"The patient's chronic smoking, hemoptysis, and elevated ACTH level that doesn't suppress with dexamethasone suggest small cell lung cancer.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02341,0.039447,0.043648,0.047919,0.055748,0.062693,0.070775,0.081701,0.093257,0.11586,0.15895,0.2066],"unified_progress":[0.027692,0.041683,0.043998,0.04852,0.054587,0.065433,0.069309,0.084573,0.097049,0.10931,0.1475